  "post_text": "📌 Detecting AI Written Code\n\nMost engineers think linter rules can catch AI-generated code 🙅‍♂️.\n\nHowever, this approach is incomplete in production environments, as it can't replace human code review 🚫.\n\nHere are the limitations:\n\n1️⃣ Linter rules are incomplete\n\n2️⃣ Code review is essential\n\n3️⃣ AI detection is hard\n\nThe core concept is that code review processes are crucial in identifying and preventing AI-generated code 📝.\n\nCode Submission -> Review -> Approval | Rejection -> Feedback\n\nBest practices in production systems involve a combination of automated tools and human review 👥.\n\nCommon mistakes include relying solely on linter rules and neglecting code review 🙅‍♂️.\n\nThe key takeaway is that a multi-faceted approach is necessary to effectively identify and prevent AI-generated code 🚀.\n\n💬 What is the most important aspect of preventing AI-generated code in production environments?\n\n#SoftwareArchitecture #CodeReview #ProductionEnvironments #CodeQuality #SoftwareEngineering #ScaleEngineering",
